==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sparse
<hw>Sparse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sparser</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sparsest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[L. <ets>sparsus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>spargere</ets> to strew, scatter. Cf. <er>Asperse</er>,
<er>Disperse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Thinly scattered; set or
planted here and there; not being dense or close together; <as>as, a
<ex>sparse</ex> population</as>.</def> <rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Placed irregularly and distantly;
scattered; -- applied to branches, leaves, peduncles, and the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sparse
<hw>Sparse</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sparsus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>spargere</ets> to scatter.]</ety> <def>To scatter; to
disperse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparsedly</ent>⟦br⟧
